{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' backend/app/models/catalog.py\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' backend/app/models/catalog.py\"", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_12", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 24, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:30:40-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' backend/app/models/catalog.py\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field, model_validator\n\n\ndef _normalize_string_list(values: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    normalized = [value.strip() for value in values if value.strip()]\n    return list(dict.fromkeys(normalized))\n\n\nclass ToneCatalogSeed(BaseModel):\n    slug: str\n    label: str\n    description: str\n    bedtime_notes: str\n    descriptors: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    default_planning_hints: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    is_active: bool = True\n\n    model_config = ConfigDict(str_strip_whitespace=True)\n\n    @model_validator(mode=\"after\")\n    def validate_fields(self) -> \"ToneCatalogSeed\":\n        self.descriptors = _normalize_string_list(self.descriptors)\n\n        if not self.descriptors:\n            raise ValueError(\"tone descriptors must contain at least one non-empty value\")\n\n        if not self.default_planning_hints:\n            raise ValueError(\"tone default_planning_hints must not be empty\")\n\n        return self\n\n\nclass GenreCatalogSeed(BaseModel):\n    slug: str\n    label: str\n    description: str\n    bedtime_safety_notes: str\n    arc_notes: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    is_active: bool = True\n    tones: list[ToneCatalogSeed] = Field(default_factory=list)\n\n    model_config = ConfigDict(str_strip_whitespace=True)\n\n    @model_validator(mode=\"after\")\n    def validate_fields(self) -> \"GenreCatalogSeed\":\n        if not self.arc_notes:\n            raise ValueError(\"genre arc_notes must not be empty\")\n\n        if not self.tones:\n            raise ValueError(\"genre tones must not be empty\")\n\n        tone_slugs = [tone.slug for tone in self.tones]\n        if len(tone_slugs) != len(set(tone_slugs)):\n            raise ValueError(f\"duplicate tone slug detected for genre {self.slug}\")\n\n        return self\n\n\nclass GenreToneCatalogDocument(BaseModel):\n    genres: list[GenreCatalogSeed] = Field(default_factory=list)\n\n    @model_validator(mode=\"after\")\n    def validate_fields(self) -> \"GenreToneCatalogDocument\":\n        if not self.genres:\n            raise ValueError(\"catalog must define at least one genre\")\n\n        genre_slugs = [genre.slug for genre in self.genres]\n        if len(genre_slugs) != len(set(genre_slugs)):\n            raise ValueError(\"duplicate genre slug detected in catalog\")\n\n        return self\n\n\nclass ToneCatalogEntry(BaseModel):\n    id: str\n    genre_id: str\n    slug: str\n    label: str\n    description: str | None = None\n    bedtime_notes: str | None = None\n    descriptors: list[str] = Field(default_factory=list)\n    default_planning_hints: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    sort_order: int\n\n\nclass GenreCatalogEntry(BaseModel):\n    id: str\n    slug: str\n    label: str\n    description: str | None = None\n    bedtime_safety_notes: str | None = None\n    arc_notes: dict[str, Any] = Field(default_factory=dict)\n    sort_order: int\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' backend/app/models/catalog.py\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_12", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 25, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:30:40-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/services/catalog.py\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "from __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nimport yaml\nfrom sqlalchemy import Select, select\nfrom sqlalchemy.orm import Session\n\nfrom app.db import Genre, ToneProfile\nfrom app.models import (\n    GenreCatalogEntry,\n    GenreCatalogSeed,\n    GenreToneCatalogDocument,\n    ToneCatalogEntry,\n    ToneCatalogSeed,\n)\n\nCATALOG_FILE_PATH = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[1] / \"data\" / \"genre_tone_catalog.yaml\"\n\n\ndef _normalize_mapping(value: Any) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        return value\n\n    return {}\n\n\ndef _normalize_string_list(value: Any) -> list[str]:\n    if isinstance(value, list):\n        return [str(item) for item in value]\n\n    return []\n\n\n@dataclass(frozen=True)\nclass CatalogSeedStats:\n    created_genres: int = 0\n    updated_genres: int = 0\n    deactivated_genres: int = 0\n    created_tones: int = 0\n    updated_tones: int = 0\n    deactivated_tones: int = 0\n\n\ndef load_catalog_document(path: Path = CATALOG_FILE_PATH) -> GenreToneCatalogDocument:\n    raw_payload = yaml.safe_load(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    return GenreToneCatalogDocument.model_validate(raw_payload or {})\n\n\ndef _build_genre_entry(row: Genre) -> GenreCatalogEntry:\n    return GenreCatalogEntry(\n        id=row.id,\n        slug=row.slug,\n        label=row.label,\n        description=row.description,\n        bedtime_safety_notes=row.bedtime_safety_notes,\n        arc_notes=_normalize_mapping(row.arc_notes),\n        sort_order=row.sort_order,\n    )\n\n\ndef _build_tone_entry(row: ToneProfile) -> ToneCatalogEntry:\n    return ToneCatalogEntry(\n        id=row.id,\n        genre_id=row.genre_id,\n        slug=row.slug,\n        label=row.label,\n        description=row.description,\n        bedtime_notes=row.bedtime_notes,\n        descriptors=_normalize_string_list(row.descriptors),\n        default_planning_hints=_normalize_mapping(row.default_planning_hints),\n        sort_order=row.sort_order,\n    )\n\n\ndef list_active_genres(session: Session) -> list[GenreCatalogEntry]:\n    stmt: Select[tuple[Genre]] = (\n        select(Genre)\n        .where(Genre.is_active.is_(True))\n        .order_by(Genre.sort_order.asc(), Genre.label.asc())\n    )\n    rows = session.execute(stmt).scalars().all()\n    return [_build_genre_entry(row) for row in rows]\n\n\ndef list_active_tones_for_genre(\n    session: Session,\n    *,\n    genre_slug: str | None = None,\n    genre_id: str | None = None,\n) -> list[ToneCatalogEntry]:\n    if genre_slug is None and genre_id is None:\n        raise ValueError(\"genre_slug or genre_id is required\")\n\n    stmt: Select[tuple[ToneProfile]] = (\n        select(ToneProfile)\n        .join(Genre, ToneProfile.genre_id == Genre.id)\n        .where(ToneProfile.is_active.is_(True), Genre.is_active.is_(True))\n        .order_by(ToneProfile.sort_order.asc(), ToneProfile.label.asc())\n    )\n\n    if genre_slug is not None:\n        stmt = stmt.where(Genre.slug == genre_slug)\n\n    if genre_id is not None:\n        stmt = stmt.where(Genre.id == genre_id)\n\n    rows = session.execute(stmt).scalars().all()\n    return [_build_tone_entry(row) for row in rows]\n\n\ndef seed_catalog(\n    session: Session,\n    catalog: GenreToneCatalogDocument,\n    *,\n    commit: bool = True,\n) -> CatalogSeedStats:\n    existing_genres = {\n        genre.slug: genre for genre in session.execute(select(Genre)).scalars().all()\n    }\n    stats = CatalogSeedStats()\n    seen_genre_slugs: set[str] = set()\n\n    for genre_index, genre_seed in enumerate(catalog.genres):\n        genre, stats = _upsert_genre(\n            session,\n            genre_seed=genre_seed,\n            genre_index=genre_index,\n            existing_genres=existing_genres,\n            stats=stats,\n        )\n        seen_genre_slugs.add(genre.slug)\n\n        existing_tones = {tone.slug: tone for tone in genre.tone_profiles}\n        seen_tone_slugs: set[str] = set()\n\n        for tone_index, tone_seed in enumerate(genre_seed.tones):\n            _tone, stats = _upsert_tone(\n                genre=genre,\n                tone_seed=tone_seed,\n                tone_index=tone_index,\n                existing_tones=existing_tones,\n                stats=stats,\n            )\n            seen_tone_slugs.add(tone_seed.slug)\n\n        for tone_slug, tone in existing_tones.items():\n            if tone_slug in seen_tone_slugs:\n                continue\n\n            if tone.is_active:\n                tone.is_active = False\n                stats = CatalogSeedStats(\n                    created_genres=stats.created_genres,\n                    updated_genres=stats.updated_genres,\n                    deactivated_genres=stats.deactivated_genres,\n                    created_tones=stats.created_tones,\n                    updated_tones=stats.updated_tones,\n                    deactivated_tones=stats.deactivated_tones + 1,\n                )\n\n    for genre_slug, genre in existing_genres.items():\n        if genre_slug in seen_genre_slugs:\n            continue\n\n        changed = False\n        if genre.is_active:\n            genre.is_active = False\n            changed = True\n\n        for tone in genre.tone_profiles:\n            if tone.is_active:\n                tone.is_active = False\n                stats = CatalogSeedStats(\n                    created_genres=stats.created_genres,\n                    updated_genres=stats.updated_genres,\n                    deactivated_genres=stats.deactivated_genres,\n                    created_tones=stats.created_tones,\n                    updated_tones=stats.updated_tones,\n                    deactivated_tones=stats.deactivated_tones + 1,\n                )\n\n        if changed:\n            stats = CatalogSeedStats(\n                created_genres=stats.created_genres,\n                updated_genres=stats.updated_genres,\n                deactivated_genres=stats.deactivated_genres + 1,\n                created_tones=stats.created_tones,\n                updated_tones=stats.updated_tones,\n                deactivated_tones=stats.deactivated_tones,\n            )\n\n    if commit:\n        session.commit()\n    else:\n        session.flush()\n\n    return stats\n\n\ndef _upsert_genre(\n    session: Session,\n    *,\n    genre_seed: GenreCatalogSeed,\n    genre_index: int,\n    existing_genres: dict[str, Genre],\n    stats: CatalogSeedStats,\n) -> tuple[Genre, CatalogSeedStats]:\n    genre = existing_genres.get(genre_seed.slug)\n    created_genres = stats.created_genres\n    updated_genres = stats.updated_genres\n\n    if genre is None:\n        genre = Genre(slug=genre_seed.slug)\n        session.add(genre)\n        existing_genres[genre_seed.slug] = genre\n        created_genres += 1\n    else:\n        updated_genres += 1\n\n    genre.label = genre_seed.label\n    genre.description = genre_seed.description\n    genre.bedtime_safety_notes = genre_seed.bedtime_safety_notes\n    genre.arc_notes = genre_seed.arc_notes\n    genre.sort_order = genre_index\n    genre.is_active = genre_seed.is_active\n\n    session.flush()\n\n    return genre, CatalogSeedStats(\n        created_genres=created_genres,\n        updated_genres=updated_genres,\n        deactivated_genres=stats.deactivated_genres,\n        created_tones=stats.created_tones,\n        updated_tones=stats.updated_tones,\n        deactivated_tones=stats.deactivated_tones,\n    )\n\n\ndef _upsert_tone(\n    *,\n    genre: Genre,\n    tone_seed: ToneCatalogSeed,\n    tone_index: int,\n    existing_tones: dict[str, ToneProfile],\n    stats: CatalogSeedStats,\n) -> tuple[ToneProfile, CatalogSeedStats]:\n    tone = existing_tones.get(tone_seed.slug)\n    created_tones = stats.created_tones\n    updated_tones = stats.updated_tones\n\n    if tone is None:\n        tone = ToneProfile(slug=tone_seed.slug)\n        genre.tone_profiles.append(tone)\n        existing_tones[tone_seed.slug] = tone\n        created_tones += 1\n    else:\n        updated_tones += 1\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/services/catalog.py\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_11", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 26, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:30:40-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml\"", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_13", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 27, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:30:40-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "# Initial genre and tone seed catalog for Storyteller.\n# Source context lives in the prompt pack:\n# - prompts/base_prompt.md\n# - prompts/12-seed-genres-and-tones.md\n# - prompts/40-genre-selection-api-and-ui.md\n# - prompts/41-tone-selection-api-and-ui.md\n# - prompts/52-bedtime-safety-and-content-guidelines.md\ngenres:\n  - slug: quest-fantasy\n    label: Quest Fantasy\n    description: A bedtime-safe adventure with a clear destination, gentle bravery, and a warm return home.\n    bedtime_safety_notes: Keep the journey wondrous rather than perilous; any danger should feel temporary, buffered by helpers, and resolved before sleep.\n    arc_notes:\n      core_arc: Leave a familiar safe place, face one meaningful but gentle challenge, and return more settled and confident.\n      tension_ceiling: Low to moderate; suspense should come from uncertainty, not threat.\n      bedtime_payoff: The final image should land in shelter, reunion, or visible rest.\n    tones:\n      - slug: hushed-wonder\n        label: Hushed Wonder\n        description: Moonlit awe, soft magic, and quiet courage lead the adventure.\n        bedtime_notes: Avoid sharp reversals or loud triumph; let discoveries feel luminous and safe.\n        descriptors:\n          - luminous\n          - moonlit\n          - gentle\n          - reverent\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: unhurried\n          conflict_style: obstacles yield through patience, observation, or kindness\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - lantern light\n            - silver water\n            - whispering leaves\n          ending_style: return home carrying a small token of wonder\n      - slug: lantern-brave\n        label: Lantern Brave\n        description: A steadier, more active quest tone where bravery feels cozy instead of intense.\n        bedtime_notes: Keep the hero's courage rooted in reassurance from mentors, companions, or familiar rituals.\n        descriptors:\n          - steady\n          - reassuring\n          - warmhearted\n          - lightly adventurous\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: steady\n          conflict_style: one central problem solved through teamwork and persistence\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - lantern glow\n            - packed satchel\n            - firelit path\n          ending_style: celebrate quietly, then settle into rest\n      - slug: fireside-reassurance\n        label: Fireside Reassurance\n        description: The quest still matters, but the emotional center stays on comfort, guidance, and safe return.\n        bedtime_notes: Let tension resolve early enough that the ending can linger in calm reflection.\n        descriptors:\n          - comforting\n          - cozy\n          - reflective\n          - sheltered\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: gentle with brief movement beats\n          conflict_style: uncertainty is eased by maps, stories, and trusted adults\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - blankets\n            - tea steam\n            - crackling fire\n          ending_style: close with gratitude, warmth, and sleep-ready quiet\n\n  - slug: gentle-mystery\n    label: Gentle Mystery\n    description: A puzzle-forward bedtime story driven by clues, curiosity, and a reassuring explanation.\n    bedtime_safety_notes: Mystery should never feel menacing; clues can be strange, but the world must stay emotionally safe and readable.\n    arc_notes:\n      core_arc: Notice a small mystery, gather clues, make a calm discovery, and restore ease.\n      tension_ceiling: Low; suspense comes from curiosity and anticipation rather than fear.\n      bedtime_payoff: The reveal should repair uncertainty and make the world feel kinder than before.\n    tones:\n      - slug: whispered-clues\n        label: Whispered Clues\n        description: Quiet, observant, and slightly magical, with clues tucked into calm nighttime details.\n        bedtime_notes: Keep the unknown intriguing instead of eerie; every clue should feel like an invitation.\n        descriptors:\n          - observant\n          - soft\n          - curious\n          - secretive\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: measured clue-by-clue progress\n          conflict_style: misdirection comes from incomplete information, not threatening forces\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - rustling curtains\n            - tiny footprints\n            - glimmering notes\n          ending_style: reveal the answer with relief and a smile\n      - slug: cozy-sleuthing\n        label: Cozy Sleuthing\n        description: Homey detective energy with snacks, family, and friendly helpers in the loop.\n        bedtime_notes: Let the investigation happen in familiar spaces with emotionally available companions.\n        descriptors:\n          - homey\n          - playful\n          - reassuring\n          - neighborly\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: brisk enough to feel engaging, but never frantic\n          conflict_style: clues are solved through conversation, memory, and shared effort\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - kitchen light\n            - padded footsteps\n            - sleepy pets\n          ending_style: finish with everyone gathered and content\n      - slug: sleepy-reveal\n        label: Sleepy Reveal\n        description: The mystery unfolds with very low stakes and an especially drowsy, comforting finish.\n        bedtime_notes: Keep the payoff tender and emotionally soothing, not twisty or shocking.\n        descriptors:\n          - drowsy\n          - tender\n          - mild\n          - glowing\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: extra calm with longer settling beats\n          conflict_style: the puzzle centers on misunderstanding, misplaced items, or hidden kindness\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - pillow forts\n            - candlelight\n            - quiet giggles\n          ending_style: reveal the answer, tuck everyone in, and fade out softly\n\n  - slug: cozy-animal-adventure\n    label: Cozy Animal Adventure\n    description: Animal characters roam, explore, and solve small problems in a world built for comfort and wonder.\n    bedtime_safety_notes: Keep animal-scale stakes manageable and end with nesting, denning, or other visible signs of safety.\n    arc_notes:\n      core_arc: Venture a short distance from comfort, learn something sweet or useful, and return to a cozy habitat.\n      tension_ceiling: Low; physical risk should be implied lightly and quickly soothed.\n      bedtime_payoff: The ending should emphasize home, family, and rhythmic natural quiet.\n    tones:\n      - slug: playful-ramble\n        label: Playful Ramble\n        description: Light-footed wandering with humor, friendly mishaps, and cheerful discovery.\n        bedtime_notes: Keep humor kind and the mishaps tiny enough that they never feel upsetting.\n        descriptors:\n          - playful\n          - spry\n          - cheerful\n          - earthy\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: light and nimble\n          conflict_style: small detours and mix-ups create movement without distress\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - mossy logs\n            - berry baskets\n            - chirping crickets\n          ending_style: everyone nestles down after a happy meander\n      - slug: nesting-comfort\n        label: Nesting Comfort\n        description: Extra soft and home-centered, with the adventure framed around making a place feel welcoming.\n        bedtime_notes: Favor emotional reassurance, caregiving, and tactile coziness over plot intensity.\n        descriptors:\n          - snuggly\n          - caring\n          - warm\n          - domestic\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: relaxed and cuddly\n          conflict_style: the problem is practical and repairable, like helping someone settle in\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - feathers\n            - quilts\n            - acorn lanterns\n          ending_style: close with everyone tucked safely into the nest or den\n      - slug: riverbank-curiosity\n        label: Riverbank Curiosity\n        description: A calm nature exploration tone with attentive observation and quiet discoveries.\n        bedtime_notes: Water, wind, and night sounds should soothe rather than unsettle.\n        descriptors:\n          - observant\n          - breezy\n          - curious\n          - natural\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: flowing with gentle pauses\n          conflict_style: curiosity leads the plot more than problem-solving does\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - reeds\n            - smooth stones\n            - drifting fireflies\n          ending_style: the river settles, then the characters do too\n\n  - slug: magical-friendship\n    label: Magical Friendship\n    description: Relationship-first stories where enchantment supports connection, trust, and emotional repair.\n    bedtime_safety_notes: Keep interpersonal conflict mild, repair visible, and magic supportive instead of chaotic.\n    arc_notes:\n      core_arc: Meet or reconnect, navigate a gentle emotional misunderstanding, and deepen the bond through care.\n      tension_ceiling: Low; the heart of the story is vulnerability, not peril.\n      bedtime_payoff: End with closeness, belonging, and a felt sense of mutual care.\n    tones:\n      - slug: tender-teamwork\n        label: Tender Teamwork\n        description: Cooperative magic and affectionate problem-solving keep the story grounded in trust.\n        bedtime_notes: Make support explicit; the characters should feel emotionally available to one another.\n        descriptors:\n          - cooperative\n          - affectionate\n          - steady\n          - bright\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: steady with shared action beats\n          conflict_style: friends solve the problem together by combining strengths\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - hand-held lanterns\n            - ribbon trails\n            - warm bread\n          ending_style: finish with a shared ritual or promise\n      - slug: sparkling-silly\n        label: Sparkling Silly\n        description: A more playful friendship mode with gentle comedy and delightfully harmless magic.\n        bedtime_notes: Keep the silliness breezy and never mean-spirited; the laugh should settle into calm.\n        descriptors:\n          - playful\n          - twinkly\n          - goofy\n          - kind\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: buoyant with short comedic beats\n          conflict_style: magical mix-ups create laughter before an easy repair\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - glittering crumbs\n            - floating hats\n            - chiming bells\n          ending_style: resolve with shared laughter, cocoa, and winding down\n      - slug: heart-mending\n        label: Heart Mending\n        description: A softer, emotionally restorative tone for stories about reconnection and reassurance.\n        bedtime_notes: Let hurt feelings be named gently and healed clearly before the ending.\n        descriptors:\n          - healing\n          - sincere\n          - warm\n          - soothing\n        default_planning_hints:\n          pacing: slow enough for emotional clarity\n          conflict_style: the obstacle is relational and eased through honesty, listening, and kindness\n          sensory_motifs:\n            - patchwork light\n            - tea cups\n            - glowing charms\n          ending_style: close on forgiveness, belonging, and sleep-ready quiet\n\n  - slug: dreamworld-voyage\n    label: Dreamworld Voyage\n    description: Drifting, surreal adventures that feel secure, beautiful, and intentionally sleepy.\n    bedtime_safety_notes: Even when dream logic gets strange, maintain orientation through comforting guides, repeated motifs, and gentle landings.\n    arc_notes:\n      core_arc: Drift into an unusual realm, explore a few dreamlike images, and descend into deeper calm.\n      tension_ceiling: Very low; dream shifts should feel curious, not destabilizing.\n      bedtime_payoff: The ending should feel like a soft arrival into sleep itself.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' backend/app/data/genre_tone_catalog.yaml\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_13", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 28, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:30:40-07:00"}
