{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"playwright|puppeteer|webapp-qa|screenshot\\\" -S frontend tools .codex -g '\"'!node_modules'\"'\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "tools/README.md:7:- `webapp-qa/`: browser automation tooling used for smoke checks and screenshots\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:2:name: webapp-qa\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:3:description: Use when interacting with a local webapp in this repo, taking screenshots, and verifying behavior both visually and functionally through the docker-compose dev stack and the bundled Puppeteer runner.\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:8:Use this skill when the task involves running the local app, exercising it in a browser, taking screenshots, or checking that UI behavior and rendered output match expectations.\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:15:4. Review the generated screenshot under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`.\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:22:## Puppeteer Specs\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:24:The reusable runner lives at `tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs`.\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:31:  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/example.png\",\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:36:    { \"action\": \"screenshot\" }\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:54:- `screenshot`\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:58:Use `tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json` for a basic smoke test plus screenshot:\n.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md:67:- For visual checks, capture a screenshot after the page reaches the expected stable state.\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:5:import puppeteer from \"puppeteer\";\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:40:async function saveFailureScreenshot(\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:42:  outputPath = \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/failure.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:46:  await page.screenshot({\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:50:  console.error(`Saved failure screenshot to ${resolvedOutputPath}`);\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:154:    case \"screenshot\": {\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:160:      await page.screenshot({\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:164:      console.log(`Saved screenshot to ${outputPath}`);\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:186:  if (process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH) {\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:187:    launchOptions.executablePath = process.env.PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH;\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:194:  const browser = await puppeteer.launch(launchOptions);\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:200:    const outputPath = spec.outputPath ?? \"./.artifacts/webapp-qa/latest.png\";\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:227:    if (!spec.steps?.some((step) => step.action === \"screenshot\")) {\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:230:      await page.screenshot({\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:234:      console.log(`Saved screenshot to ${resolvedOutputPath}`);\ntools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:243:      await saveFailureScreenshot(page);\ntools/webapp-qa/package.json:2:  \"name\": \"storyteller-webapp-qa\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package.json:11:    \"puppeteer\": \"^24.0.0\"\ntools/webapp-qa/Dockerfile:3:ENV PUPPETEER_SKIP_DOWNLOAD=true\ntools/webapp-qa/Dockerfile:9:WORKDIR /workspace/tools/webapp-qa\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-session-route.spec.json:3:  \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-session-route.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-session-route.spec.json:26:      \"action\": \"screenshot\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-keyboard-focus.spec.json:21:      \"action\": \"screenshot\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-keyboard-focus.spec.json:23:      \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-24-focus-skip-link.png\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-keyboard-focus.spec.json:34:      \"action\": \"screenshot\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-keyboard-focus.spec.json:36:      \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-24-focus-brand-link.png\"\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:2:  \"name\": \"storyteller-webapp-qa\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:8:      \"name\": \"storyteller-webapp-qa\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:11:        \"puppeteer\": \"^24.0.0\"\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:37:    \"node_modules/@puppeteer/browsers\": {\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:39:      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/@puppeteer/browsers/-/browsers-2.13.0.tgz\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:813:    \"node_modules/puppeteer\": {\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:815:      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/puppeteer/-/puppeteer-24.40.0.tgz\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:820:        \"@puppeteer/browsers\": \"2.13.0\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:824:        \"puppeteer-core\": \"24.40.0\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:828:        \"puppeteer\": \"lib/cjs/puppeteer/node/cli.js\"\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:834:    \"node_modules/puppeteer-core\": {\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:836:      \"resolved\": \"https://registry.npmjs.org/puppeteer-core/-/puppeteer-core-24.40.0.tgz\",\ntools/webapp-qa/package-lock.json:840:        \"@puppeteer/browsers\": \"2.13.0\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-home-mobile.spec.json:25:      \"action\": \"screenshot\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-home-mobile.spec.json:27:      \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-24-home-mobile.png\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-foundation-flow.spec.json:25:      \"action\": \"screenshot\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-foundation-flow.spec.json:27:      \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-24-home-desktop.png\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-foundation-flow.spec.json:58:      \"action\": \"screenshot\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-24-foundation-flow.spec.json:60:      \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-24-workspace-desktop.png\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json:3:  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/homepage.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json:26:      \"action\": \"screenshot\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-home-route.spec.json:3:  \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-home-route.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-home-route.spec.json:26:      \"action\": \"screenshot\"\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage-workflow-contract.spec.json:3:  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/homepage-workflow-contract.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage-workflow-contract.spec.json:30:      \"action\": \"screenshot\"\nfrontend/package-lock.json:4018:        \"@vitest/browser-playwright\": \"4.1.2\",\nfrontend/package-lock.json:4036:        \"@vitest/browser-playwright\": {\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-not-found-route.spec.json:3:  \"outputPath\": \"../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-20-not-found-route.png\",\ntools/webapp-qa/examples/prompt-20-not-found-route.spec.json:22:      \"action\": \"screenshot\"\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"rg -n \\\"playwright|puppeteer|webapp-qa|screenshot\\\" -S frontend tools .codex -g '\"'!node_modules'\"'\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_202", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 382, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:52:13-07:00"}
{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "The repo has its own `webapp-qa` runner, so I\u2019m switching the browser pass onto that path. I\u2019m keeping the visual-QA workflow, but using the project\u2019s bundled Puppeteer spec runner instead of hand-rolled shell snippets.", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_204", "text": "The repo has its own `webapp-qa` runner, so I\u2019m switching the browser pass onto that path. I\u2019m keeping the visual-QA workflow, but using the project\u2019s bundled Puppeteer spec runner instead of hand-rolled shell snippets.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 383, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:52:20-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_205", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 384, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:52:22-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "---\nname: webapp-qa\ndescription: Use when interacting with a local webapp in this repo, taking screenshots, and verifying behavior both visually and functionally through the docker-compose dev stack and the bundled Puppeteer runner.\n---\n\n# Webapp QA\n\nUse this skill when the task involves running the local app, exercising it in a browser, taking screenshots, or checking that UI behavior and rendered output match expectations.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Start the local stack with `docker compose up -d --build`.\n2. Confirm the app is healthy with `docker compose ps`.\n3. Run browser checks from the `browser` service with `docker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec <spec-path>`.\n4. Review the generated screenshot under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`.\n\n## App URLs\n\n- From the host machine, the app is available at `http://localhost:8566`.\n- From inside the browser container, use `http://frontend:8566`.\n\n## Puppeteer Specs\n\nThe reusable runner lives at `tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs`.\n\nSpecs are JSON files with this shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"url\": \"http://frontend:8566\",\n  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/example.png\",\n  \"viewport\": { \"width\": 1440, \"height\": 960 },\n  \"steps\": [\n    { \"action\": \"waitForSelector\", \"selector\": \"[data-testid='app-card']\" },\n    { \"action\": \"assertText\", \"text\": \"Hello from FastAPI!\" },\n    { \"action\": \"screenshot\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nSupported actions:\n\n- `goto`\n- `waitForSelector`\n- `waitForText`\n- `click`\n- `type`\n- `press`\n- `hover`\n- `assertSelector`\n- `assertText`\n- `assertUrlIncludes`\n- `waitForTimeout`\n- `screenshot`\n\n## Example\n\nUse `tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json` for a basic smoke test plus screenshot:\n\n```bash\ndocker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec ./examples/homepage.spec.json\n```\n\n## Verification Guidance\n\n- For functional checks, prefer explicit `assertText`, `assertSelector`, and URL assertions over informal observation.\n- For visual checks, capture a screenshot after the page reaches the expected stable state.\n- If a page depends on backend data, verify the user-visible result instead of only checking network readiness.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_205", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 385, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:52:22-07:00"}
