{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "failed, exit 1: /bin/zsh -lc 'docker exec -w /workspace/tools/webapp-qa storyteller-browser-1 npm run check -- --spec ../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-40-genre-desktop.spec.json'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "[browser:debug] [vite] connecting...\n[browser:debug] [vite] connected.\n[browser:info] %cDownload the React DevTools for a better development experience: https://react.dev/link/react-devtools font-weight:bold\nSaved screenshot to /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-40-genre-desktop-before.png\nSaved failure screenshot to /workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/failure.png\nError: Expected text not found: \"Tune the bedtime mood\"\nCurrent page text:\nSkip to main content\n\nBEDTIME STORY STUDIO\n\nStoryteller\nSessions\nWorkspace\n\nResume existing stories or open a session workspace when you are ready to continue.\n\nCONNECTION\n\nBackend reachability\nLast checked 1:57 AM.\nOnline\nCheck again\n\nThe app shell is connected to FastAPI through the Vite development proxy.\n\nHello from FastAPI!\n\nSESSION WORKSPACE\n\nPrompt 40 Desktop QA Rerun\n\nChat and stage-driven workflow controls now share one persistent surface, with the left lane reserved for conversation and the right canvas reserved for structured editing.\n\nCurrent stage\nGenre\nSave status\nSaved Apr 2, 1:56 AM\nSession ID\n912d947d-0ca5-4c5e-bc10-c14aef6929d0\nLive updates\nIdle\n\nSet VITE_SESSION_EVENTS_WS_URL to enable live updates.\n\nQueued\nReturn home\nLive feed idle\nIn progress\n\nThe workspace is running from the durable snapshot only. Configure the websocket endpoint to start session-scoped live updates.\n\nChat lane\n\nMessages, action echoes, and redirect notes stay visible beside the structured workflow.\n\nLive feed idle\n\nReady for notes, approvals, and stage edits from the conversation lane.\n\nSystem\nApr 2, 1:56 AM\n\nSession opened. Resume at Genre.\n\nMessage composer\n\nSend approvals, nudges, or revision notes without leaving the current workspace stage.\n\nReady\nQuick actions\n\nRun a common action in one tap, or type the slash version.\n\nCommands\nNext stage\nSummarize plan\n\nSlash commands: /next-stage, /plan\n\nMessage composer\n\nPress Enter to send. Press Shift+Enter for a new line. Try /next-stage, /plan.\n\n0/1200 characters\n\nSend message\nWorkflow canvas\n\nThe main pane keeps enough width for forms, stage review, and later composition or audio progress views.\n\nQueued\nStage navigator\n\nEvery required workflow step is visible now, with URL-backed panel selection that can coexist with backend-owned stage truth.\n\n01\n\nSTAGE 01\n\nGenre\n\nChoose the overall bedtime-story lane before the rest of the plan is shaped.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\nThis is the durable current stage saved by the backend.\n02\n\nSTAGE 02\n\nTone\n\nChoose the emotional texture and bedtime-safety posture for the session.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n03\n\nSTAGE 03\n\nStory brief\n\nCapture the user's free-form idea and any normalized planning summary derived from it.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n04\n\nSTAGE 04\n\nPitches\n\nGenerate, compare, refine, and accept candidate story directions.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n05\n\nSTAGE 05\n\nCharacters\n\nDefine the accepted character sheet that later planning and writing will reference.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n06\n\nSTAGE 06\n\nBeat sheet\n\nStore the accepted Save-the-Cat beat sheet for the session.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n07\n\nSTAGE 07\n\nStory setup\n\nStore soft planning targets such as word count, runtime, and chapter structure.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n08\n\nSTAGE 08\n\nComposition\n\nWrite the story durably in segments, with room for interruption and targeted rewrites.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n09\n\nSTAGE 09\n\nAudio\n\nConfigure narration settings and generate resumable audio artifacts.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n10\n\nSTAGE 10\n\nFinalize\n\nRead, listen, review final assets, and download exports.\n\nQueued\nLocked\nLocked stages stay previewable without implying they are editable yet.\n\nSTAGE SCAFFOLD\n\nChoose a bedtime genre lane\n\nThis panel will become the curated genre catalog, with clear guardrails about how each lane shapes the rest of the story workflow.\n\nQueued\nUnlocked\n\nThe route and the durable session stage are aligned. Live editors and job views can mount here later without changing the URL pattern.\n\nCurrent lane\n\nGenre pending\n\nPick a bedtime lane to ground the rest of the planning workflow.\n\nBedtime guardrail\n\nA calm story arc comes built in\n\nEvery entry in this catalog is pre-vetted for calm stakes, emotional repair, and a safe landing before sleep.\n\nNext step\n\nTone selection comes next\n\nChoose a genre to unlock tone choices next.\n\nChoose from the catalog\n\nThe catalog is seeded with bedtime-safe lanes, so the user picks from a curated set instead of inventing a genre from scratch.\n\nCurated bedtime genres\n\nThese cards come from the seeded catalog, with short descriptions, bedtime safety notes, and arc guidance for what comes next.\n\nRequired\n01\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nQuest Fantasy\n\nA bedtime-safe adventure with a clear destination, gentle bravery, and a warm return home.\n\nAvailable\nLow to moderate; suspense should come from uncertainty, not threat.\nARC\nLeave a familiar safe place, face one meaningful but gentle challenge, and return more settled and confident.\nSAFETY NOTE\nKeep the journey wondrous rather than perilous; any danger should feel temporary, buffered by helpers, and resolved before sleep.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n02\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nGentle Mystery\n\nA puzzle-forward bedtime story driven by clues, curiosity, and a reassuring explanation.\n\nAvailable\nLow; suspense comes from curiosity and anticipation rather than fear.\nARC\nNotice a small mystery, gather clues, make a calm discovery, and restore ease.\nSAFETY NOTE\nMystery should never feel menacing; clues can be strange, but the world must stay emotionally safe and readable.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n03\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nCozy Animal Adventure\n\nAnimal characters roam, explore, and solve small problems in a world built for comfort and wonder.\n\nAvailable\nLow; physical risk should be implied lightly and quickly soothed.\nARC\nVenture a short distance from comfort, learn something sweet or useful, and return to a cozy habitat.\nSAFETY NOTE\nKeep animal-scale stakes manageable and end with nesting, denning, or other visible signs of safety.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n04\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nMagical Friendship\n\nRelationship-first stories where enchantment supports connection, trust, and emotional repair.\n\nAvailable\nLow; the heart of the story is vulnerability, not peril.\nARC\nMeet or reconnect, navigate a gentle emotional misunderstanding, and deepen the bond through care.\nSAFETY NOTE\nKeep interpersonal conflict mild, repair visible, and magic supportive instead of chaotic.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n05\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nDreamworld Voyage\n\nDrifting, surreal adventures that feel secure, beautiful, and intentionally sleepy.\n\nAvailable\nVery low; dream shifts should feel curious, not destabilizing.\nARC\nDrift into an unusual realm, explore a few dreamlike images, and descend into deeper calm.\nSAFETY NOTE\nEven when dream logic gets strange, maintain orientation through comforting guides, repeated motifs, and gentle landings.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n06\n\nGENRE OPTION\n\nSoft Science Wonder\n\nScience-flavored bedtime stories driven by curiosity, observation, and awe rather than technical complexity.\n\nAvailable\nLow; the challenge should be intellectual or practical, not dangerous.\nARC\nNotice a natural or cosmic question, explore it with gentle experimentation, and end with bigger wonder plus calm understanding.\nSAFETY NOTE\nKeep scientific concepts accessible, reassuring, and emotionally warm; discovery should never become sterile or high-pressure.\n\nChoosing this genre narrows the tone list for the next step.\n\nChoose genre\n\nProgress\n\nWorkflow progress\n0 of 10 stages complete\n\nResume at Genre with 0% of the workflow currently complete.\n\nStory lane\n\nGenre pending / Tone pending\n\nThe structured brief, pitch, and beat choices will accumulate here as the session advances.\n\nProduction\n\nGenre\n\nComposition and audio controls will take over this area once the planning stages are complete.\n    at assertText (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:66:11)\n    at async runStep (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:137:7)\n    at async main (file:///workspace/tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs:224:7)\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'docker exec -w /workspace/tools/webapp-qa storyteller-browser-1 npm run check -- --spec ../../.artifacts/webapp-qa/prompt-40-genre-desktop.spec.json'", "exit_code": 1, "id": "item_269", "status": "failed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 507, "prompt_index": 41, "prompt_name": "40 \u2014 Genre Selection API and UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-01T18:57:28-07:00"}
